  "texts": [
    "Brief self-control scale for middle school studentsSelf-control capability was assessed using the Brief Self-Control Scale for Middle School Students [31].",
    "The scale's reliability and validity have been confirmed in previous research, making it suitable for evaluating selfcontrol among middle school students [32].",
    "This scale consists of 10 items rated on a Likert 5-point scale, where higher scores indicate lower self-control capabilities.",
    "The Cronbach's alpha coefficient for the scale in this study was 0.81.",
    "Difficulties in emotion regulation scale-short formEmotion regulation difficulties were measured using the Difficulties in Emotion Regulation Scale-Short Form (DERS-16) [33]."
  ],
